<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556347>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Eurynome longimana Stimpson, 1857, male (cl 8.5 mm, cw 5.9 mm) (ZRC 2020.378), Mozambique. A, overall view; B, ventral view of cephalothorax; C, lateral view of cephalothorax; D, outer view of right chela." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5556347/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556351>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Eurynome longimana Stimpson, 1857, male (cl 8.5 mm, cw 5.9 mm) (ZRC 2020.378), Mozambique. A, dorsal view of anterior half of carapace; B, ventral view showing antennules, antennae, epistome and buccal cavity; C, right fourth ambulatory leg (partially denuded); D, right third maxilliped; E, pleon." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5556351/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556389>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. A–C, Eurynome longimana Stimpson, 1857. A, B, female, South Africa; C, male (cl 14.0 mm, cl 10.0 mm), South Africa; D–F, Eurynome longimana Stimpson, 1857, male (cl 8.5 mm, cw 5.9 mm) (ZRC 2020.378), Mozambique; G, Choniognathus reini (Balss, 1924), female (cl 9.1 mm, cw 6.0 mm) (USNM 48204), Korea; H, C. reini (Balss, 1924), ovigerous female (cl 6.3 mm, cw 4.0 mm) (ZRC 2020.373), Philippines; I–K, Seiitaoides mirabilis n. sp., holotype male (cl 13.2 mm, cw 7.3 mm) (MNHN-IU-2010-1301), Madagascar.A, dorsal view of carapace and enlarged boletiform tubercle; B, right P5 merus; C, G1; D, I, left G1 (ventral view); E, J, left G1 (dorsal view); F, K, left G2; G, H, left third maxilliped.A–C after Barnard (1950: fig. 12a–c). G, from original figure by T. Naruse. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5556389/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556353>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Eurynome aspera (Pennant, 1777). A–E, male (cl 14.4 mm, cw 10.7 mm) (ZRC 1988.666), Mediterranean; F, male (cl 12.4 mm, cw 11.5 mm) (ZRC 1988.665), Mediterranean. A, overall view; B, F, right third maxilliped; C, ventral view of cephalothorax; D, right third ambulatory leg (partially denuded); E, right fourth ambulatory leg (partially denuded)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5556353/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

